      "id": "RecentPost25366",
      "post_content": "This is what I want to see in vanilla creatures. When 2/2-for-two cards have been repeatedly obsoleted(and at common, no less), it's almost become a necessity to slightly boost power and/or toughness for NOT having an ability. Yes, it's nice to be able to compare a card to Grizzly Bears to determine how good it is (ie. \"Oh, it's a Hill Giant with flash\" or \"Grizzly Bears with a top hat\"), but usually the value of a card is obvious from the get-go. Even if [Air Elemental](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Air Elemental) didn't exist to compare [Diijn of Wishes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Diijn of Wishes) to, the Diijn would still be a good card.\n  \n   \nSo this? Perfect. Now, doing it rarely on the one-mana side is probably for the best- I'm looking at you, [Savannah Lions](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savannah Lions). But since most creatures are abilitied-up anyway, it's not so much of a problem if it starts showing up in the lower cost range.",
      "posted_by": "DoctorKenneth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"RecentPost25366\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">This is what I want to see in vanilla creatures. When 2/2-for-two cards have been repeatedly obsoleted(and at common, no less),  it's almost become a necessity to slightly boost power and/or toughness for NOT having an ability. Yes, it's nice to be able to compare a card to Grizzly Bears to determine how good it is (ie. \"Oh, it's a Hill Giant with flash\" or \"Grizzly Bears with a top hat\"), but usually the value of a card is obvious from the get-go. Even if <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Air Elemental\">Air Elemental</a> didn't exist to compare <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Diijn of Wishes\">Diijn of Wishes</a> to, the Diijn would still be a good card.\r<br/> <br/>So this? Perfect. Now, doing it rarely on the one-mana side is probably for the best- I'm looking at you, <a class=\"autoCard\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Savannah Lions\">Savannah Lions</a>. But since most creatures are abilitied-up anyway, it's not so much of a problem if it starts showing up in the lower cost range.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_recentPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: <a class=\"postedByLink\" href=\"javascript:void(0);\" id=\"PostedBy1392\">DoctorKenneth</a>\r\n                                (9